# Neon headings

**Where it lives**

- **Styles:** `_includes/css/index.css` — `@keyframes neon-frame-edges`, `neon-flicker-g1`…`g3`, `neon-ember-crack`, `neon-ember-fall`; rules under `main h1, main h2` and `.neon-tube*`.
- **Behavior:** `_includes/js/neon-headings.js` — splits plain `main h1`/`main h2` text into up to four `.neon-tube` spans (group 0 steady, 1–3 flicker); sets random `--neon-spark-x` / `--neon-spark-y` on an interval derived from computed **`--neon-ember-duration`**.

**When changing timing**

- Prefer editing **`main h1, main h2`** custom properties: `--neon-frame-duration`, `--neon-flicker-g*-duration`, `--neon-flicker-g*-delay`, `--neon-ember-duration`. Avoid duplicating the ember duration in JS.
- If you change **ember keyframe percentages** (`neon-ember-crack` / `neon-ember-fall`), keep them in sync with each other; the JS interval still follows `--neon-ember-duration` only.

**When changing structure**

- Headings with **child elements** (e.g. links) or existing `.neon-tube` are skipped by the script.
- User-facing docs: **`README.md`** section “Neon headings”.
